As far as problems with your code go, here are a few:

- `getElementsTagName` isn&#39;t a real function
- `getElementsByTagName` returns a collection - you want to iterate over them if you want to apply styles. For example: `Array.from(document.getElementsByTagName(&quot;a&quot;)).map(x =&gt; x.style.color = &quot;red&quot;)`
- If you want only one thing to be affected, give it a unique id so only that thing is targeted, with `document.querySelector(&quot;#&lt;WHATEVER&gt;&quot;)` or `document.getElementById(&quot;&lt;WHATEVER&gt;&quot;)`
- You&#39;re adding an event listener to variable `a`, then declaring a new variable `b` in exactly the same way and trying to do something to it. I&#39;ve removed the duplicate stuff
- Your div isn&#39;t closed properly

